<node id="&quot;ANGLE OF HIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Angle of His is the acute angle created between the cardia at the entrance to the stomach and the esophagus, forming a valve to prevent reflux."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CARDIA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cardia is the opening of the stomach that connects to the esophagus, forming part of the Angle of His."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ESOPHAGUS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Esophagus is the muscular tube connecting the throat to the stomach, through which food passes during swallowing."&lt;SEP&gt;"Esophagus is the tube that can be inflamed by refluxed stomach contents, a complication of GERD."&lt;SEP&gt;"Esophagus is the tube that connects the mouth to the stomach, forming part of the Angle of His."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00d8a90928192bc1e43da7ca8973145f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STOMACH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stomach is a muscular, hollow organ in the digestive system that stores and processes food, producing acid and enzymes to aid digestion."&lt;SEP&gt;"Stomach is the organ in dogs where bile-induced inflammation can lead to bilious vomiting syndrome."&lt;SEP&gt;"Stomach is the organ that receives food from the esophagus and is connected to the esophagus via the cardia, forming part of the Angle of His."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00d8a90928192bc1e43da7ca8973145f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DUODENAL BILE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Duodenal bile is bile produced in the duodenum that can cause inflammation if it refluxes into the esophagus."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENZYMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Enzymes are substances that help break down food in the stomach and can cause inflammation if they reflux into the esophagus."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STOMACH ACID&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stomach acid helps digest food but can cause inflammation if it refluxes into the esophagus."&lt;SEP&gt;"Stomach acid is a strong acid produced by the stomach to aid in digestion, which can cause damage if it flows back into the esophagus."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00d8a90928192bc1e43da7ca8973145f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLLAR SLING FIBRES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Collar sling fibres are muscles that form part of the Angle of His and help create the valve preventing reflux."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CIRCULAR MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Circular muscles around the gastroesophageal junction form part of the Angle of His and help create the valve preventing reflux."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GASTROESOPHAGEAL REFLUX DISEASE (GERD)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DISEASE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD) is a condition where stomach acid frequently flows back into the tube connecting your mouth and stomach (esophagus), causing discomfort."&lt;SEP&gt;"Gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD) is a long-term condition where stomach contents come back up into the esophagus, causing various symptoms and complications."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dce4942e1d1ba86ce4d2351d2837cc82&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STOMACH CONTENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stomach contents include acid, bile, and enzymes that can cause inflammation if they reflux into the esophagus."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ESOPHAGITIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DISEASE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Esophagitis is a complication of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)."&lt;SEP&gt;"Esophagitis is an inflammation of the esophagus, a complication of GERD."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ESOPHAGEAL STRICTURES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DISEASE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Esophageal strictures are a complication of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)."&lt;SEP&gt;"Esophageal strictures are a condition where there is narrowing of the esophagus, which can cause difficulty in swallowing."&lt;SEP&gt;"Esophageal strictures are narrowed areas in the esophagus, a complication of GERD."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dce4942e1d1ba86ce4d2351d2837cc82&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BARRETT'S ESOPHAGUS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DISEASE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Barrett's esophagus is a complication of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)."&lt;SEP&gt;"Barrett's esophagus is a condition where the cells lining the esophagus change due to chronic acid exposure, a complication of GERD."&lt;SEP&gt;"Barrett's esophagus is a condition where the cells lining the lower part of the esophagus change due to damage from stomach acid, often caused by chronic acid reflux."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dce4942e1d1ba86ce4d2351d2837cc82&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BILIOUS VOMITING SYNDROME&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DISEASE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bilious vomiting syndrome is a condition characterized by vomiting in response to bile-induced inflammation of the stomach, also known as reflux gastritis syndrome and duodenal-gastric reflux. Bile salts interfere with the gastric mucosal barrier, causing irritation and gastritis."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bilious vomiting syndrome is a condition in dogs characterized by vomiting in response to bile-induced inflammation of the stomach."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dce4942e1d1ba86ce4d2351d2837cc82&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BILE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bile is a substance produced in the liver and stored in the gallbladder, which can cause inflammation in the stomach and lead to bilious vomiting syndrome."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bile is a substance produced in the liver and stored in the gallbladder, which can cause inflammation in the stomach."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TASTE OF ACID&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SYMPTOM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Taste of acid is a symptom of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEARTBURN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SYMPTOM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Heartburn is a burning sensation in the chest caused by stomach acid flowing back into the esophagus, often relieved by Alka-Seltzer."&lt;SEP&gt;"Heartburn is a symptom of acid indigestion characterized by a burning sensation in the chest or throat."&lt;SEP&gt;"Heartburn is a symptom of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00d8a90928192bc1e43da7ca8973145f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BAD BREATH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SYMPTOM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bad breath is a symptom of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHEST PAIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SYMPTOM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Chest pain is a symptom of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOMITING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SYMPTOM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vomiting is a symptom of bilious vomiting syndrome in dogs."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vomiting is a symptom of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BREATHING PROBLEMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SYMPTOM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Breathing problems are a symptom of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WEARING AWAY OF THE TEETH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SYMPTOM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Wearing away of the teeth is a symptom of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BILE-INDUCED INFLAMMATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bile-induced inflammation is a condition that can cause bilious vomiting syndrome in dogs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INFLAMMATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Inflammation is a condition that can be caused by bile-induced inflammation in the stomach."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LIVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Liver is the organ that produces bile, which can cause inflammation in the stomach."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GALLBLADDER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gallbladder is the organ that stores bile, which can cause inflammation in the stomach."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DUODENUM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Duodenum is the first part of the small intestine where bile is produced and stored, which can cause inflammation if it refluxes into the esophagus."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2461f8617cfb6b94cd6c576c31386a48</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPOKESTOON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Spokestoon is a term used to describe an established cartoon character hired to endorse a product, distinct from characters invented specifically for product identity."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dce4942e1d1ba86ce4d2351d2837cc82</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIATUS HERNIA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hiatus hernia is a medical condition where abdominal organs, typically the stomach, slip through the diaphragm into the chest, leading to symptoms such as GERD, LPR, trouble swallowing, and chest pains. Complications may include iron deficiency anemia, volvulus, or bowel obstruction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dce4942e1d1ba86ce4d2351d2837cc82</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANGELIC ACID&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Angelic acid is a monocarboxylic unsaturated organic acid primarily found in plants of the family Apiaceae, named after the plant Angelica archangelica from which it was first isolated by German pharmacist Ludwig Andreas Buchner in 1842. It has a biting taste and pungent sour odor and exists as the 'cis' isomer of 2-methyl-2-butenoic acid, which can convert to tiglic acid under certain conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Angelic acid is a monocarboxylic unsaturated organic acid primarily found in plants of the family Apiaceae."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dce4942e1d1ba86ce4d2351d2837cc82</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARYNGOPHARYNGEAL REFLUX (LPR)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Laryngopharyngeal reflux (LPR) is a condition where stomach acid flows up into the throat, causing irritation and symptoms such as a bitter taste in the mouth, coughing, and hoarseness."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dce4942e1d1ba86ce4d2351d2837cc82</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IRON DEFICIENCY ANEMIA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Iron deficiency anemia is a condition characterized by a lack of iron in the body, leading to a reduced number of red blood cells or hemoglobin."&lt;SEP&gt;"Iron deficiency anemia is a condition where the body does not have enough healthy red blood cells to carry oxygen to the body's tissues, often resulting from chronic bleeding or poor dietary intake of iron."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dce4942e1d1ba86ce4d2351d2837cc82</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOLVULUS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Volvulus is a condition where a loop of intestine twists around itself, cutting off the blood supply and causing severe pain and other complications."&lt;SEP&gt;"Volvulus is a condition where a loop of intestine twists around itself, cutting off the blood supply and causing severe pain and other symptoms."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dce4942e1d1ba86ce4d2351d2837cc82</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BOWEL OBSTRUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bowel obstruction is a condition where the contents of the intestines cannot pass through normally, often causing severe pain, bloating, and vomiting."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bowel obstruction is a condition where the passage of contents through the intestines is blocked, causing severe abdominal pain and other symptoms."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dce4942e1d1ba86ce4d2351d2837cc82</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TUMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tums is an antacid product manufactured by GlaxoSmithKline, available in both regular and sugar-free versions. It is sold over-the-counter at various retail stores and provides relief from acid indigestion, heartburn, and indigestion."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLAXOSMITHKLINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"GlaxoSmithKline is a multinational pharmaceutical company responsible for manufacturing Tums, an antacid product."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ST. LOUIS, MISSOURI, USA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"St. Louis, Missouri, USA is the location where Tums is manufactured by GlaxoSmithKline."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GARDEN ANGELICA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PLANT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Garden angelica, scientifically known as Angelica archangelica, is a plant from the family Apiaceae, from which angelic acid was first isolated."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUCROSE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CHEMICAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sucrose is a disaccharide composed of glucose and fructose, commonly known as table sugar, used as a sweetener in Tums."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 102}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CALCIUM CARBONATE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CHEMICAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Calcium carbonate (CaCO3) is a chemical compound used as the active ingredient in Tums to neutralize stomach acid."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 102}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INDIGESTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Indigestion is a condition characterized by discomfort in the upper abdomen, often relieved by medications like Alka-Seltzer."&lt;SEP&gt;"Indigestion is a condition characterized by discomfort or pain in the upper abdomen, often accompanied by bloating, gas, and nausea."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00d8a90928192bc1e43da7ca8973145f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PAINS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SYMPTOM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pains refer to various types of discomfort or pain experienced by patients, which can be alleviated by angelic acid esters in herbal medicines."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SYMPTOM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fever is a body temperature elevated above normal, often treated with medications like Alka-Seltzer."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fever is a symptom characterized by an elevated body temperature, often associated with infections or other health issues."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00d8a90928192bc1e43da7ca8973145f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GOUT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gout is a form of inflammatory arthritis caused by the deposition of uric acid crystals in the joints, leading to severe pain and swelling."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUGAR FREE VERSION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PRODUCT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sugar free version of Tums is a variant of the antacid product without sucrose, providing the same relief from acid indigestion, heartburn, and indigestion."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b26176724ec22e6b117a1e128710e5e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLLIS GASTROPLASTY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Collis gastroplasty is a surgical procedure designed to create a Nissen fundoplication when the esophagus is too short."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-096cc11d3301b70aece52c3c93a2c211</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RETAIL STORES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Retail stores are places where consumers can purchase over-the-counter drugs, including drug stores, grocery stores, and mass merchandisers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-096cc11d3301b70aece52c3c93a2c211</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;A COLLIS GASTROPLASTY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Collis gastroplasty is a surgical procedure involving the creation of a Nissen fundoplication when the esophagus is too short, utilizing a vertical incision in the stomach to lengthen the esophagus and reduce acid reflux."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-00d8a90928192bc1e43da7ca8973145f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NISSEN FUNDOPLICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PROCEDURE"</data>
