  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The United States experiences approximately 1 million cases of salmonellosis annually, with notable outbreaks such as the 2012 outbreak that infected over 1800 people."&lt;SEP&gt;"The United States is a country where Kaiser Permanente operates, highlighting its extensive reach."&lt;SEP&gt;"The United States is a country where WWE Network initially launched and where it later expanded."&lt;SEP&gt;"The United States is the country where Ernestine Jean Russell later became an American citizen and coach."&lt;SEP&gt;"The United States is the country where Medicaid operates and where PCCM programs are implemented by state Medicaid agencies."&lt;SEP&gt;"The United States is the country where Medicare and Medicare Advantage programs operate, and where the Aetna Health Inc. v. Davila case took place."&lt;SEP&gt;"The United States is the country where Timothy Hollingsworth represented in the Bocuse d'Or world final."&lt;SEP&gt;"The United States is the country where Virginia Abernethy ran for Vice President and where the American Freedom Party operates."&lt;SEP&gt;"The United States is the setting of The Last of Us, where Joel and Ellie travel."&lt;SEP&gt;"United States is a country where Medicaid managed care programs operate, involving state Medicaid agencies and MCOs to provide healthcare services to beneficiaries."</data>
