  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 108}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THE STATE OF TEXAS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The State of Texas is the jurisdiction enforcing the THCLA and allowing certain types of insurance to be regulated within its borders."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TEXAS STATUTE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Texas statute allows for compensatory or punitive damages to redress losses or deter future transgressions, distinguishing it from ERISA § 1132."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ERISA § 1132&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"ERISA § 1132 is a federal law that does not allow for compensatory or punitive damages, affecting the enforcement of certain insurance policies."&lt;SEP&gt;"ERISA § 1132 is a specific section of the Employee Retirement Income Security Act that does not allow for compensatory or punitive damages."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THCLA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Texas Healthcare Liability Act (THCLA) allows the State of Texas to enforce certain decisions, particularly in cases not preempted by ERISA."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Texas Healthcare Liability Act (THCLA) is a state law that allows the State of Texas to enforce certain decisions, particularly in cases not preempted by ERISA."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 107}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 157}, {"level": 3, "cluster": 160}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GOVERNMENT-SPONSORED PLANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Government-sponsored plans include Medicare, Medicaid, Federal, State, Municipal Employee, Church-sponsored, or Individual Health Plan Policies, which are not preempted by ERISA."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 107}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 157}, {"level": 3, "cluster": 160}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERSTATE COMMERCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Interstate Commerce is a constitutional power that allows the federal government to regulate commerce between states, used as a basis for ERISA's jurisdiction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 110}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ERISA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"ERISA (Employee Retirement Income Security Act) is a federal law enacted in 1974 that regulates pension and other employee benefit plans, particularly those involving multiple states."&lt;SEP&gt;"ERISA (Employee Retirement Income Security Act) is a federal law that regulates pension and other employee benefit plans."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 110}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PRIVATE AND SELF-PAY INSURANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Private and Self-Pay Insurance includes High-deductible individual policies, self-pay, and any insurance not subsidized by a private employer, which are exempt from ERISA's preemption."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 110}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENHANCED PRIMARY CARE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Enhanced Primary Care is a title or topic related to the broader context of healthcare regulation and managed care."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 108}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMPENSATORY DAMAGES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Compensatory damages are monetary awards intended to compensate the injured party for actual losses or injuries."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PUNITIVE DAMAGES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Punitive damages are monetary awards intended to punish the defendant for particularly egregious conduct and deter similar behavior in the future."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PRIVATE EMPLOYERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Private employers are entities that provide Health Benefit plans and are subject to ERISA regulations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MEDICARE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Medicare is a federal health insurance program for people aged 65 and older, as well as younger people with disabilities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 107}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 158}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MEDICAID&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Medicaid is a U.S. government healthcare service that oversees the system of managed care used by state Medicaid agencies, focusing on primary care providers and enrolled beneficiaries."&lt;SEP&gt;"Medicaid is a joint federal and state program that helps with medical costs for some low-income people and people with disabilities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e40d0bd6c25f1a0f78cc71fd88f7b0ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 103}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEDERAL, STATE, MUNICIPAL EMPLOYEE PLANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"These are health insurance plans provided to employees of federal, state, and municipal governments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHURCH-SPONSORED PLANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Church-sponsored plans are health insurance plans provided by religious organizations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INDIVIDUAL HEALTH PLAN POLICIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Individual Health Plan Policies are health insurance plans purchased by individuals, including high-deductible individual policies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIGH-DEDUCTIBLE INDIVIDUAL POLICIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"High-deductible individual policies are health insurance plans with higher deductibles, often paired with Health Savings Accounts (HSAs)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SELF-PAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Self-pay refers to patients paying for healthcare services out-of-pocket without insurance coverage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STATE OF TEXAS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The State of Texas is a U.S. state that enforces the THCLA and allows certain types of insurance to be regulated within its borders."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMPENSATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Compensation refers to the act of making amends for a wrong or injury, often through monetary awards."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DETERRENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Deterrence refers to the prevention of future misconduct through the threat of punishment or penalties."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEGLIGENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Negligence refers to a failure to exercise the appropriate level of care, resulting in harm to others."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TEXAS HEALTHCARE LIABILITY ACT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Texas Healthcare Liability Act (THCLA) is a state law that allows the State of Texas to enforce certain decisions, particularly in cases not preempted by ERISA."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Texas Healthcare Liability Act allows for accountability of Managed Care entities in cases of negligence."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e40d0bd6c25f1a0f78cc71fd88f7b0ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9da95c787d3fcf42b176c577484a8ab</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 106}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 156}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PRIVATE EMPLOYER PLANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Private Employer Plans are health insurance plans provided by private employers, which are subject to ERISA regulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Private Employer Plans are insurance plans that are not regulated by individual states, unlike Medicaid plans."</data>
